# OWASP Scanner — Full Implementation Checklist

> **Project**: `Owasp_Scanner_Final`  
> **Goal**: Unify `Owasp_Scanner_1` + `Owasp_Scanner_2` into one scanning engine, wire all UI features end-to-end, ensure Docker tooling works, and implement advanced features.

---

## Phase 1 — Unified Scanner Engine (Merge Scanner_1 + Scanner_2) ✅ COMPLETE

- [x] **1.1 Audit & compare both scanners**
  - [x] Map all modules in `Owasp_Scanner_1/analyzers/` (18 modules) vs `Owasp_Scanner_2/` (23 modules)
  - [x] Identify overlapping modules (misconfig, injection, frontend_js, secrets_engine, semantic, endpoint_extractor, etc.)
  - [x] Identify modules unique to Scanner_2 (auth_scanner, broken_access, cloud_misconfig, api_security, supply_chain, insecure_design, integrity_scanner, analysis, findings, formatters, patterns, enums)
  - [x] Identify modules unique to Scanner_1 (exception_scanner, logging_scanner, sensitive_data_exposure, owasp_scanner orchestrator)
  - [x] Compare `core/engine.py` (1022 lines) vs `Owasp_Scanner_2/engine.py` (842 lines) — merge best of both

- [x] **1.2 Create unified scanner package**
  - [x] Create `scanner_engine/` at project root as the unified package
  - [x] Merge `core/engine.py` — combine `scan_file()`, `scan_directory()`, score calculators from both versions
  - [x] Merge all analyzer modules into `scanner_engine/` (via orchestrator imports)
  - [x] Merge models — UnifiedFinding model in orchestrator.py
  - [x] Merge reporters — OWASP coverage mapping in owasp_coverage.py
  - [x] Port rules/patterns from both scanners (574 total patterns)
  - [x] Create unified `__init__.py` with clean public API (v5.0.0)

- [x] **1.3 Implement orchestration pipeline**
  - [x] Build `orchestrator.py` that chains Scanner_1 modules → Scanner_2 modules → SSRF
  - [x] Phase 1 scan: Run Scanner_2 analyzers (11 modules: misconfig, injection, frontend_js, endpoint, auth, access_control, cloud, api_security, supply_chain, insecure_design, integrity)
  - [x] Phase 2 scan: Run Scanner_1 analyzers (3 modules: logging, exception, sensitive_data)
  - [x] Phase 3 scan: Run new SSRF scanner (1 module)
  - [x] Deduplicate findings across all phases (md5-based dedup keeping highest confidence)
  - [x] Merge and normalize all findings into unified `UnifiedFinding` model
  - [x] Compute combined risk scores (overall_score, severity_counts, owasp_coverage)
  - [x] 6 scan profiles: quick (5), standard (10), full (15), owasp-top-10 (10), cloud (4), api (5)

- [x] **1.4 Update backend imports**
  - [x] Update `backend/main.py` MODULE_REGISTRY to use unified package (`scanner_engine.orchestrator`)
  - [x] Replace `_run_module_scan()` with orchestrator's `run_module_scan()`
  - [x] Replace local `normalize_finding()` with orchestrator's `normalize_finding_to_dict()`
  - [x] Add all new OWASP modules to MODULE_REGISTRY (logging, exception, sensitive_data, ssrf — total 15 modules)
  - [x] Add `/api/v1/profiles` endpoint for scan profile listing
  - [x] Add `/api/v1/health` updated to v5.0 with full engine metadata
  - [x] Enhanced `/api/v1/scan/start` with profile-based module resolution

- [x] **1.5 Full OWASP Top 10:2025 coverage**
  - [x] A01:2025 — Broken Access Control → `broken_access.py` (45 patterns)
  - [x] A02:2025 — Cryptographic Failures → `frontend_js_analyzer.py` + `sensitive_data_exposure.py` (157 patterns)
  - [x] A03:2025 — Injection → `injection_scanner.py` (90 patterns)
  - [x] A04:2025 — Insecure Design → `insecure_design.py` (25 patterns)
  - [x] A05:2025 — Security Misconfiguration → `misconfig_engine.py` + `cloud_misconfig.py` (90 patterns)
  - [x] A06:2025 — Vulnerable & Outdated Components → `supply_chain.py` (20 patterns)
  - [x] A07:2025 — Identification & Auth Failures → `auth_scanner.py` (35 patterns)
  - [x] A08:2025 — Software & Data Integrity Failures → `integrity_scanner.py` (20 patterns)
  - [x] A09:2025 — Security Logging & Monitoring Failures → `logging_scanner.py` (10 patterns)
  - [x] A10:2025 — Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) → **NEW** `ssrf_scanner.py` (15 patterns)

- [x] **1.6 Smoke Testing** (added)
  - [x] Created `test_unified_engine.py` with 8 comprehensive tests
  - [x] All 8 tests passing: imports, registry, profiles, scanning, normalization, dedup, scoring, OWASP coverage
  - [x] OWASP coverage mapping validated: 10 categories, 70 unique CWEs, 574 patterns

