## Phase 3 — Backend-to-Frontend Real-Time Scanning Pipeline ✅ COMPLETE

- [x] **3.1 SSE (Server-Sent Events) streaming**
  - [x] Verify `/api/v1/scan/{scan_id}/stream` endpoint in `main.py` works end-to-end
  - [x] Ensure real-time finding events stream as modules complete
  - [x] Stream progress updates (module name, % complete, elapsed time)
  - [x] Stream severity counts as they are updated
  - [x] Emit scan completion/error events

- [x] **3.2 REST API endpoints**
  - [x] `POST /api/v1/scan` — Initiate new scan (connect to unified engine)
  - [x] `GET /api/v1/scan/{scan_id}` — Get scan status & results
  - [x] `GET /api/v1/scan/{scan_id}/findings` — Get paginated findings
  - [x] `GET /api/v1/scans` — List user's scan history
  - [x] `DELETE /api/v1/scan/{scan_id}` — Cancel running scan
  - [x] `GET /api/v1/scan/{scan_id}/report` — Download scan report (JSON/HTML/PDF)
  - [x] `GET /api/v1/modules` — List available scanner modules with status

- [x] **3.3 Frontend API client**
  - [x] Create/update `src/lib/api.ts` with typed API client
  - [x] Implement SSE event listener for real-time scan updates
  - [x] Add error handling and retry logic
  - [x] Add authentication token injection (from Firebase auth)
  - [x] Create React hooks: `useScan()`, `useScanHistory()`, `useScanStream()`

- [x] **3.4 Finding normalization**
  - [x] Ensure all scanner modules output consistent finding shape
  - [x] Map every finding to OWASP category, CWE, severity, remediation
  - [x] Store normalized findings in PostgreSQL `findings` table
  - [x] Cache active scan state in Redis for real-time streaming

